1
00:00:01,830 --> 00:00:03,870
Instructor: The publishable and the secret key

2
00:00:03,870 --> 00:00:05,850
that we have for our Stripe,

3
00:00:05,850 --> 00:00:08,280
we need to add that in our project.

4
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:11,823
That way we can access them whenever we want to.

5
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:14,880
Now, when we have to add any connection

6
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:17,700
or any secrets in the application,

7
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:22,113
I will be doing that inside app settings dot JSON file.

8
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:24,720
Now typically in production,

9
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,790
you might be using a secret vault

10
00:00:26,790 --> 00:00:29,280
or other details for your secrets,

11
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:32,103
but app settings is a good place to get started.

12
00:00:33,390 --> 00:00:36,810
We already added our database connection here,

13
00:00:36,810 --> 00:00:40,680
so I will be creating a new section for Stripe.

14
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:42,660
Let me call that Stripe.

15
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:45,780
And inside there I want two things.

16
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:47,970
One is a secret key

17
00:00:47,970 --> 00:00:52,020
and the next one here will be publishable key.

18
00:00:52,020 --> 00:00:54,450
Let me navigate to Stripe here,

19
00:00:54,450 --> 00:00:56,670
copy the publishable key.

20
00:00:56,670 --> 00:00:58,650
I will paste it here,

21
00:00:58,650 --> 00:01:00,660
reveal the secret key,

22
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:03,750
and we will paste that right here.

23
00:01:03,750 --> 00:01:06,270
Secret key starts with an SK

24
00:01:06,270 --> 00:01:09,513
and publishable key starts with a PK.

25
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:12,900
Perfect, that looks good.

26
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:15,420
Next thing, what we can do is we can directly

27
00:01:15,420 --> 00:01:19,080
get the section by using the eye configuration,

28
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:22,230
but I want to show you a slightly different way

29
00:01:22,230 --> 00:01:26,280
of fetching some values from app settings.

30
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:29,460
What we can do is we can create a utility file

31
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:33,060
for Stripe settings based on the exact property name

32
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:34,500
that are right here,

33
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,653
like secret key and publishable key.

34
00:01:38,610 --> 00:01:41,400
I think it is better if I show you

35
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,680
inside the utility project.

36
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:45,930
Let me create a new class.

37
00:01:45,930 --> 00:01:50,163
I will call that Stripe settings dot cs.

38
00:01:51,666 --> 00:01:54,070
It'll be a public class here

39
00:01:55,170 --> 00:01:58,380
and inside there I will create two properties,

40
00:01:58,380 --> 00:02:00,780
which will have the exact spelling

41
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:03,030
like we have in the name here,

42
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:06,183
which is secret key and publishable key.

43
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:11,520
Then what we can do is inside the program dot cs

44
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,560
we can configure in a manner

45
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:17,790
that secrets in app settings are automatically injected

46
00:02:17,790 --> 00:02:19,593
inside these properties.

47
00:02:20,490 --> 00:02:22,353
Let me show you how to do that.

48
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:29,060
Right here we can say builder dot services dot configure

49
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:33,780
and there we want to configure Stripe settings.

50
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:37,200
Now, next, how do we want to configure that?

51
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,770
For that we will say builder dot configuration

52
00:02:40,770 --> 00:02:43,110
dot get section,

53
00:02:43,110 --> 00:02:46,320
and we have to write the section name,

54
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:50,460
name of the section, if you remember, that is Stripe,

55
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:53,973
but it is always safe to copy and paste that.

56
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,880
Now, as long as the property names

57
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:59,220
inside the Stripe settings match

58
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:03,390
what is there in the Stripe section in app settings

59
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:06,810
it'll automatically inject these values

60
00:03:06,810 --> 00:03:09,603
inside the properties right here.

61
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:12,180
So that is another way

62
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:16,290
of fetching the values from your app settings.

63
00:03:16,290 --> 00:03:18,870
Now how and when we will use that,

64
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:22,350
that we will cover in the upcoming videos,

65
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:26,970
but right now in our packages we have not even added Stripe.

66
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:29,040
So what we have to do is first

67
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:33,090
we have to add the NuGet package for Stripe.

68
00:03:33,090 --> 00:03:37,920
Right click on the project, manage NuGet packages here,

69
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:42,570
and in the browse tab we will search for Stripe dot net.

70
00:03:42,570 --> 00:03:44,550
Now, when it comes to Stripe

71
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:47,070
I do not want the pre-release package.

72
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:49,200
So let me install the stable one,

73
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:52,893
which is 41.9 as of this recording.

74
00:03:55,890 --> 00:03:57,780
Perfect, it has been installed

75
00:03:57,780 --> 00:04:01,353
and with that Stripe has been added in the project.

76
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,470
When we are using Stripe,

77
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:06,450
one thing that we have to configure

78
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:10,470
in program dot cs is the API key

79
00:04:10,470 --> 00:04:13,440
and that API key is the secret key

80
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:15,783
inside app settings dot JSON.

81
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:20,459
So scroll down where we have the middleware here.

82
00:04:20,459 --> 00:04:24,243
We have to configure Stripe configuration,

83
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:26,370
type that,

84
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:28,440
and if you press control dot,

85
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:31,830
we have the using statement for Stripe.

86
00:04:31,830 --> 00:04:35,340
There, we have to configure the API key.

87
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:40,340
This API key is the secret key in app settings dot JSON.

88
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:43,860
Now we have already populated the Stripe settings,

89
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:46,680
but that we will use in controller.

90
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,080
Right now we have the builder object,

91
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:54,080
so on builder dot configuration we have get section.

92
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:56,580
We will write Stripe here.

93
00:04:56,580 --> 00:04:59,520
That will retrieve the complete section,

94
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:02,430
but inside the section of Stripe,

95
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:04,530
we found secret key.

96
00:05:04,530 --> 00:05:08,730
So let me copy that and we will separate that by a colon

97
00:05:08,730 --> 00:05:11,100
and paste the value.

98
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:15,720
That will actually go inside Stripe, get the secret key,

99
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:18,180
and on there we will say get

100
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:21,600
and type of the value is string.

101
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,580
That will fetch the value

102
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:27,660
and assign that to the Stripe configuration.

103
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:31,530
With that, Stripe has been configured in our project

104
00:05:31,530 --> 00:05:34,920
and we have also configured the connection strings

105
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:38,193
for secret key and publishable key.

